1. Project Summary

I built an AI-powered music recommendation system that works like a simplified Spotify-style discovery engine. The system recommends songs using a combination of semantic understanding (NLP transformers) and
audio feature intelligence, then merges both signals into a hybrid ranking system.

The main idea was to go beyond simple keyword matching and instead understand:

what the user means (mood, vibe, intent)
what the song sounds like (audio features like energy, danceability, valence)

The final system delivers personalized recommendations with album covers and 30-second previews using the Deezer API.

2. Objective

The goal of this project was to:

Build a hybrid AI recommendation system for music discovery
Combine text-based understanding + audio-based features
Improve recommendation quality using transformer embeddings
Create an interactive Streamlit web app
Simulate a real-world recommendation engine like Spotify

