# Questions

1. What problem does my project solve?

 It solves the problem of poor personalization in basic music recommenders by combining semantic understanding and audio feature analysis.

2. Why did i use a hybrid model?

Because text-only models are shallow and audio-only models miss context. A hybrid approach balances both meaning and sound quality.

3. What is Sentence-BERT used for?

It converts song metadata into embeddings so the system can understand semantic similarity between songs and user queries.

4. What makes my system different from Spotify-style recommenders?

My system is explainable, hybrid-based, and integrates real-time previews with mood-aware ranking instead of only collaborative filtering.

5. How do i handle unknown or rare inputs?

I use fallback mechanisms like genre clustering and semantic similarity search to ensure results are always returned.

6. Why combine audio features with NLP?

Because music is both emotional and structural — NLP captures meaning, while audio features capture sound behavior.

7. What was the most difficult part?

Balancing similarity scores and preventing biased recommendations while maintaining diversity in results.

8. What is the real-world use case?

It can be used in streaming platforms, personalized playlists, AI DJs, and music discovery engines.


